ZH: 钙是人体中重要的营养物质。
EN: Calcium is an important nutrient for the human body.

ZH: 食物中富含钙的食材有哪些？
EN: What are some foods rich in calcium?

ZH: 骨骼健康需要充足的钙。
EN: Healthy bones require sufficient calcium.

ZH: 奶制品是一种很好的钙源。
EN: Dairy products are a good source of calcium.

ZH: 钙对婴儿和儿童发育尤为重要。
EN: Calcium is especially important for the development of babies and children.

ZH: 蔬菜和豆类也是不错的钙来源。
EN: Vegetables and legumes are also good sources of calcium.

ZH: 每天确保摄入足够的钙很重要。
EN: It is important to ensure an adequate intake of calcium every day.

ZH: 钙能促进肌肉收缩和放松。
EN: Calcium can promote muscle contraction and relaxation.

ZH: 缺乏钙会导致骨质疏松。
EN: A lack of calcium can lead to osteoporosis.

ZH: 钙还可以帮助维持心脏健康。
EN: Calcium can also help maintain heart health.

ZH: 成年人每天建议摄取1000毫克的钙。
EN: It is recommended that adults consume 1000 milligrams of calcium per day.

ZH: 丰富的蛋白质可以增加人体对钙的吸收率。
EN: A diet rich in protein can increase the body's absorption rate of calcium.

ZH: 钙可以帮助维持牙齿健康。
EN: Calcium can help maintain healthy teeth.

ZH: 钙还对维持神经传导有益。
EN: Calcium is also beneficial for maintaining nerve conduction.

ZH: 每种钙补充剂都有自己的吸收速度。
EN: Each calcium supplement has its own absorption rate.

ZH: 阳光是补充维生素D所需的最佳方式，从而有助于钙的吸收。
EN: Sunlight is the best way to supplement vitamin D, which helps in the absorption of calcium.

ZH: 运动有助于维持骨骼中的钙平衡。
EN: Exercise helps maintain calcium balance in the bones.

ZH: 钙盐沉积在血管壁上可能导致心血管疾病。
EN: Deposits of calcium salts on the walls of blood vessels can lead to cardiovascular disease.

ZH: 孕妇需要额外的钙以支持胎儿的生长。
EN: Pregnant women need extra calcium to support the growth of the fetus.

ZH: 大豆制品是素食者的主要钙来源之一。
EN: Soy products are one of the main sources of calcium for vegetarians.
